The paper deals with the impact of spatial correlation on the performance of 3D MIMO systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of covariance matrices and channel models, which are relevant to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
